title: "List All Tabs" button reappears after being removed when switching tab groups
content:
Hello,

I’m using Firefox together with the "Simple Tab Groups" extension. When I remove the "List All Tabs" button from the toolbar (right-click → “Remove from Toolbar”), it disappears as expected. However, after switching between tab groups in Simple Tab Groups, the button automatically reappears on the toolbar.

Is there a way to completely prevent this button from returning, even in such cases? I would like it to remain removed permanently until I manually restore it.

If there is currently no way to achieve this, is it something that could be expected in future browser updates?

Thank you in advance for your help!

Best regards, Dmitrii
creator: DIM-9000

title: What is the Best method to backup IMAP email accounts?
content: The best method to archive or back up IMAP email accounts is by using a professional tool like the MailsDaddy IMAP Backup Tool. This software works with popular services such as Gmail, Yahoo, Zoho, AOL, and others, allowing you to securely export emails into formats like PST, MBOX, EML, MSG, HTML, and MHTML. It preserves the original folder hierarchy, email metadata, attachments, and formatting, and includes filters to back up specific date ranges or folders. The tool supports all Windows versions and provides a free trial for up to 20 emails per mailbox, with paid licenses for larger needs. This ensures a quick, safe, and complete backup of your IMAP data.

title: to linkedin
content: Dear LinkedIn Support, I hope you are doing well. I am writing to address the restrictions on my account, which I understand are due to concerns about the name associated with my profile. I would like to clarify that the name used is a variation of my name, which is commonly used in informal, non-professional situations in my country. In many regions, including my own, it is perfectly acceptable to use a shortened form or familiar variation of your full name on personal platforms such as LinkedIn, as long as the name does not violate any guidelines. The name displayed on my account represents an informal way of addressing my family, friends, and acquaintances, and is not intended to mislead or confuse anyone. I assure you that my account has always complied with LinkedIn's rules and is secure. I kindly request that my case be reviewed and my account be reinstated. Thank you for taking the time to accept our understanding. Thank you for your attention to this matter, and I look forward to your response. Best regards
creator: kastrogerma

title: How to stop websites removing the history of the back button?
content: There are many websites (I noticed with Google, Instagram) that seem to remove the list of previous pages. They obviously want to prevent that visitors go back (for example to the search results) and proceed somewhere else. The result is that I click on a link, the linked page loads and then clicking on the back button does nothing, as if I entered the URL directly into the address bar. I consider that a terrible user experience because websites are trying to control my options, even on domains before I reached their sites. Since one of the huge advantages of Firefox is the claim that that it helps users take back control, I hope that there is a way how to prevent visited websites from manipulating the history, which is outside their own domains. I am aware that I could open the history or type in the address of the previous page again, but it is just not the same as pressing the back button. Is there any configuration (or add-on) that could help? Thanks!
creator: mozilla446

title: 短縮URLが開けない
content: Twitterで使用されている「t.co」等の短縮URLにアクセス出来ず、「アクセスしようとしているサイトを見つけられません」とエラーが表示されます。 他のブラウザだとアクセス出来る為、Firefoxの設定の問題だと思うのですが、解消方法が分かりません。 解消方法をご存知な方はいらっしゃいますでしょうか。
creator: xig.hikarun

title: Firefox Synch backup from online
content:
Salve, ho un problema grave e non so come rimediare e ripartire da 0 è veramente frustrante.

Io ho sempre usato FireFox Synch attivo e avevo tutti i segnalibri, password ecc che avrebbero dovuto essere mandati (cioè erano spuntati ) ho dovuto formattare il pc senza aver la possibilità di usare il vecchio hard disk quindi non ho potuto fare un backup manuale o recupero su un altro dispositivo (C:\Users\wolfe\AppData\Roaming\Mozilla\Firefox\Profiles ecc )

volevo chiedere se vi risulta dei salvataggi online da dove partire prima del 10/08/2025, perchè attualmente anche accedendo sembra che non ci siano segnalibri password o altro avrei una versione del 2021 da google chrome però perderei più di 4 anni di siti salvati

vi prego non c'è altro modo in caso mancante? ho provato Recuva, niente da fare purtroppo backup manuali non ci avevo minimamente pensato dato il synch

Grazie del supporto
creator: zagzigzagoon

title: password help to many
content: With the password settings for my domain, it seems to count the saved passwords as if they are for the same account, even though they are different. It also doesn’t show an image or label to indicate which account each password belongs to.
creator: dmchartac

title: Need Help getting out of "Bookmark"!
content: When in Firefox, I have a list of ICONS I can choose from. I also have News, etc., under my ICONS that I can look at before I go on to the ICON I want to check out. In one of those News items, I checked "Bookmark" so I could get back to it later. In so doing, it took me to my Bookmark page, but wouldn't let me get back to my Firefox page I have my icons on. Help Please!
creator: judylchurch
